## 1. mbuzz — Best for Validated Attribution

**Why consider mbuzz:** Most attribution tools tell you what they think happened. mbuzz proves it with incrementality testing.

### What mbuzz Offers

**Server-side attribution that ad blockers can't touch.** While Triple Whale relies on client-side tracking that misses 30% of visitors, mbuzz tracks events on your backend—capturing 95%+ of customer journeys.

**8 attribution models, not 3.** Compare first-touch, last-touch, linear, time-decay, U-shaped, W-shaped, plus data-driven Markov Chain and Shapley Value models side-by-side. See how credit shifts between channels under different models.

**Custom models via simple DSL.** Don't wait for feature requests—write your own attribution logic in minutes:

```ruby
# Weight branded search lower, boost first organic touch
model "my_custom_model" do
  if channel == "organic" && position == :first
    weight 1.5
  elsif channel == "paid_search" && query.branded?
    weight 0.25
  else
    weight :linear
  end
end
```

**LTV attribution built-in.** mbuzz tracks every recurring payment back to its original acquisition source. That Facebook campaign might look great at first purchase but terrible at 12-month LTV—you'll know the difference.

**Pricing that makes sense:**

| Tier | Events/Month | Price |
|------|-------------|-------|
| Free | Up to 50K | $0 |
| Starter | Up to 1M | $29/mo |
| Growth | Up to 5M | $99/mo |
| Pro | Up to 25M | $299/mo |

**10-minute setup** with native SDKs for Rails, Django, Laravel, and Node.js. No tag managers, no JavaScript debugging.

