## 2. Northbeam — Best for Enterprise DTC

**Why consider Northbeam:** ML-powered attribution that prevents over-counting. Best for brands spending $500K+/month on paid media.

### Northbeam vs Triple Whale

| Factor | Triple Whale | Northbeam |
|--------|-------------|-----------|
| Target size | SMB-Mid | Enterprise ($40M+) |
| Attribution method | Rule-based | ML fractional credit |
| Over-attribution | Can occur | Prevented (sums to 100%) |
| Predictive analytics | Limited | ✓ Included |
| Pricing | Revenue-based | Pageview-based ($400+/mo) |
| Learning curve | Low | High |

### Why Northbeam Over Triple Whale

Northbeam solves the over-attribution problem. When your platforms claim 190 conversions for 100 actual sales, Northbeam assigns fractional credit that sums to exactly 100.

The tradeoff: it's complex, expensive, and designed for dedicated media buying teams.

### Best For

- DTC brands at $40M+ revenue
- Teams with dedicated media buyers
- Those frustrated with platform overcounting
- Sophisticated budget optimization needs

**Also consider:** [Northbeam alternatives](/articles/northbeam-alternatives) if Northbeam is too enterprise for your needs.

